{{use dmy dates|date=January 2018}} {{Infobox person | image = | name = Julien Carette | birth_name = Julien Henri Carette | birth_date = {{Birth date|1897|12|23|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Paris]], France | death_date = {{Death date and age|1966|7|20|1897|12|23|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Saint-Germain-en-Laye]], France | occupation = Actor | yearsactive = 1931–1964}}
'''Julien Henri Carette''' (23 December 1897 &ndash; 20 July 1966) was a French film actor. He appeared in 127 films between 1931 and 1964. He suffered fatal burns when his nylon shirt caught fire from his cigarette; apparently he had fallen asleep while smoking.{{cn|date=February 2018}}
==Selected filmography== {{Div col|colwidth=30em}} * ''[[George and Georgette]]'' (1934) * ''[[My Heart Is Calling You]]'' (1934) * ''[[Dora Nelson (1935 film)|Dora Nelson]]'' (1935) * ''[[Fanfare of Love]]'' (1935) * ''[[Marinella (film)|Marinella]]'' (1936) * ''[[27 Rue de la Paix]]'' (1936) * ''[[Grand Illusion (film)|Grand Illusion]]'' (1937) * ''[[La Bête Humaine (film)|La Bête Humaine]]'' (1938) * ''[[La Marseillaise (film)|La Marseillaise]]'' (1938) * ''[[Coral Reefs (film)|Coral Reefs]]'' (1939) * ''[[The Rules of the Game]]'' (1939) * ''[[Behind the Facade]]'' (1939) * ''[[Thunder Over Paris]]'' (1940) * ''[[Goodbye Leonard]]'' (1943) * ''[[Madly in Love (1943 film)|Madly in Love]]'' (1943) * ''[[Service de nuit]]'' (1944) * ''[[Keep an Eye on Amelia]]'' (1949) * ''[[Night Round]]'' (1949) * ''[[Une si jolie petite plage]]'' (1949) * ''[[The Winner's Circle (1950 film)|The Winner's Circle]]'' (1950) * ''[[Without Leaving an Address]]'' (1951) * ''[[His Last Twelve Hours]]'' (1951) * ''[[Bernard and the Lion]]'' (1951) * ''[[Matrimonial Agency]]'' (1952) * ''[[Au diable la vertu]]'' (1953) * ''[[What Scoundrels Men Are! (1953 film)|What Scoundrels Men Are!]]'' (1953) * ''[[Fraternité (TV)]]'' (1954) * ''[[House of Ricordi]]'' (1954) * ''[[I'll Get Back to Kandara]]'' (1956) * ''[[Meeting in Paris]]'' (1956) * ''[[Si Paris nous était conté]]'' (1956) * ''[[Archimède le clochard]]'' (1959) * ''[[The Green Mare (film)|The Green Mare]]'' (1959) {{Div col end}}
